t: Psalm 22
To the chief Musician upon Aijeleth Shahar, A Psalm of David.
My*p God, my God, why hast thou forsaken me? why art thou so far from helping me, and from the words of my roaring?
O*p my God, I cry in the daytime, but thou hearest not; and in the night season, and am not silent.
But*p thou art holy, O thou that inhabitest the praises of Israel.
Our*p fathers trusted in thee: they trusted, and thou didst deliver them.
They*p cried unto thee, and were delivered: they trusted in thee, and were not confounded.
But*p I am a worm, and no man; a reproach of men, and despised of the people.
All*p they that see me laugh me to scorn: they shoot out the lip, they shake the head, saying,
He*p trusted on the Lord*s that he would deliver him: let him deliver him, seeing he delighted in him.
But*p thou art he that took me out of the womb: thou didst make me hope when I was upon my mother's breasts.
I*p was cast upon thee from the womb: thou art my God from my mother's belly.
Be*p not far from me; for trouble is near; for there is none to help.
Many*p bulls have compassed me: strong bulls of Bashan have beset me round.
They*p gaped upon me with their mouths, as a ravening and a roaring lion.
I*p am poured out like water, and all my bones are out of joint: my heart is like wax; it is melted in the midst of my bowels.
My*p strength is dried up like a potsherd; and my tongue cleaveth to my jaws; and thou hast brought me into the dust of death.
For*p dogs have compassed me: the assembly of the wicked have inclosed me: they pierced my hands and my feet.
I*p may tell all my bones: they look and stare upon me.
They*p part my garments among them, and cast lots upon my vesture.
But*p be not thou far from me, O Lord:*s O my strength, haste thee to help me.
Deliver*p my soul from the sword; my darling from the power of the dog.
Save*p me from the lion's mouth: for thou hast heard me from the horns of the unicorns.
I*p will declare thy name unto my brethren: in the midst of the congregation will I praise thee.
Ye*p that fear the Lord,*s praise him; all ye the seed of Jacob, glorify him; and fear him, all ye the seed of Israel.
For*p he hath not despised nor abhorred the affliction of the afflicted; neither hath he hid his face from him; but when he cried unto him, he heard.
My*p praise shall be of thee in the great congregation: I will pay my vows before them that fear him.
The*p meek shall eat and be satisfied: they shall praise the Lord*s that seek him: your heart shall live for ever.
All*p the ends of the world shall remember and turn unto the Lord:*s and all the kindreds of the nations shall worship before thee.
For*p the kingdom is the Lord's:*s and he is the governor among the nations.
All*p they that be fat upon earth shall eat and worship: all they that go down to the dust shall bow before him: and none can keep alive his own soul.
A*p seed shall serve him; it shall be accounted to the Lord for a generation.
They*p shall come, and shall declare his righteousness unto a people that shall be born, that he hath done this.
